cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with detecting human actions in videos. The use of weak supervision and exploiting video-specific and dataset-wide statistics also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of standard benchmarks and datasets suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
